The Tamil Tigers embarked on a tour to garner support for peace talks in Sri Lanka.
Swiss officials met with rebel leaders to discuss a federal structure for peace negotiations.
Factional violence within the Tigers has hindered progress in the peace process.
The rebels released some members on bail, signaling a potential shift towards reconciliation.
Japanese envoy Yasushi Akashi is working to revive stalled peace talks between the government and the rebels.
Despite challenges, efforts are ongoing to bring all parties back to the negotiating table for the sake of lasting peace in Sri Lanka.
